00:40:51.436 --> 00:40:53.609
Squash him.

507
00:40:54.605 --> 00:40:55.777
His name is Dean.

508
00:40:55.940 --> 00:40:57.908
We like Dean.

509
00:40:58.735 --> 00:41:00.078
Dean.

510
00:41:01.720 --> 00:41:05.621
So... Where'd, uh, where'd he come from?

511
00:41:06.117 --> 00:41:07.619
He doesn't remember.

512
00:41:07.785 --> 00:41:10.083
He's like a little kid.

513
00:41:10.246 --> 00:41:12.624
Little. Yeah.

514
00:41:12.790 --> 00:41:15.293
Wait a minute. 
You can talk to him?

515
00:41:15.460 --> 00:41:19.431
Kinda. He can't say a lot of words yet
but he understands things pretty good.


516
00:41:19.589 --> 00:41:21.606
Oh, yeah. I see.

517
00:41:25.470 --> 00:41:28.144
He needs food and shelter.

518
00:41:40.985 --> 00:41:44.159
You got plenty of room here.
This place is perfect.


519
00:41:44.322 --> 00:41:45.539
Go away.

520
00:41:45.698 --> 00:41:49.168
I can have him push the door down.
You know I can.


521
00:41:49.327 --> 00:41:51.671
Hogarth. I can't hide it here.

522
00:41:51.829 --> 00:41:53.831
- "Him," not "it."
- Whatever.


523
00:41:53.998 --> 00:41:56.217
You don't even know where "he" came from

524
00:41:56.375 --> 00:41:58.628
or, or what the hell "he" is!

525
00:41:58.795 --> 00:42:00.513
He's my friend.

526
00:42:01.464 --> 00:42:04.183
Yeah, what am I? 
Am I your friend?

527
00:42:04.342 --> 00:42:06.515
Bring some Franken-bot with
out-of-state plates over here,


528
00:42:06.677 --> 00:42:08.520
make me change my tune.

529
00:42:08.679 --> 00:42:11.523
I don't like that jazz. God, I'm tired.

530
00:42:11.682 --> 00:42:13.525
So, he can stay?

531
00:42:13.684 --> 00:42:17.655
Tonight. Tomorrow, I don't know.
I don't know about tomorrow.


532
00:42:26.697 --> 00:42:28.370
Sleep tight.

533
00:42:28.533 --> 00:42:30.535
I'll see you tomorrow.

534
00:42:44.715 --> 00:42:46.888
- You're up already?
- Just making the bed.


535
00:42:47.051 --> 00:42:50.772
That's nice. Come downstairs.
I have a surprise for you.


536
00:42:55.393 --> 00:42:57.942
Morning, sport. Sleep well?

537
00:42:58.104 --> 00:42:59.731
Mom?

538
00:43:00.398 --> 00:43:03.743
Isn't it wonderful, Hogarth?
We finally rented our room.


539
00:43:03.901 --> 00:43:06.620
Ugh. I'm not very hungry.

540
00:43:13.911 --> 00:43:16.414
Oh, yeah.

541
00:43:18.416 --> 00:43:20.464
Hello, this is Hogarth Hughes speaking.
Who's calling, please?


542
00:43:20.626 --> 00:43:23.095
I said he could stay the night, kid.

543
00:43:23.254 --> 00:43:24.301
It's morning now.

544
00:43:24.463 --> 00:43:26.465
Look, I'll try to come over, okay?

545
00:43:26.632 --> 00:43:28.930
But there's this weird guy here
who's watching me.


546
00:43:29.093 --> 00:43:30.219
What's that supposed to mean?

547
00:43:30.386 --> 00:43:33.936
I got this big, giant...
Giant thing out here.


548
00:43:34.098 --> 00:43:36.942
- I can't talk right now, okay? Bye.
- Hogarth!


549
00:43:37.101 --> 00:43:38.978
Who was that, sport? 
Friend of yours?

550
00:43:39.145 --> 00:43:41.318
Yeah. He's, uh, a new kid.

551
00:43:41.647 --> 00:43:46.278
What... I...
Hey, hey! Stop! Stop that! Stop it!


552
00:43:47.653 --> 00:43:50.406
Hey, mind if I ask you a few
questions there, buckaroo?


553
00:43:50.573 --> 00:43:53.622
Now, why would you tell your mom
about a giant robot, slugger?


554
00:43:53.784 --> 00:43:55.457
Say, what'd you see at the power station?
Huh, tiger?


555
00:43:55.620 --> 00:43:57.964
You tell anyone else about this, buddy?
How big is this thing, ranger?


556
00:43:58.122 --> 00:43:59.419
Been in the forest lately?
Hey. Where you going?


557
00:43:59.582 --> 00:44:01.255
Champ? Slugger? Hey, cowboy?
Where you goin'?


558
00:44:01.417 --> 00:44:03.795
- Where you goin'?
- I'm going out!


559
00:44:03.961 --> 00:44:06.931
Why don't you take Mr. Mansley with you?
Show him the sights.


560
00:44:07.089 --> 00:44:08.966
Oh, Mom, the sights?

561
00:44:09.133 --> 00:44:12.770
Hey, I'd love that. Give us a chance to get
acquainted, swap some stories, huh, chief?


562
00:44:12.929 --> 00:44:15.023
There are two kinds
of metal in this yard.

563
00:44:15.181 --> 00:44:16.808
Scrap and art.

564
00:44:16.974 --> 00:44:19.318
If you gotta eat one of them,
eat the scrap.


565
00:44:19.477 --> 00:44:23.948
What you currently have
in your mouth is art!


566
00:44:27.610 --> 00:44:28.657
Art?

567
00:44:34.784 --> 00:44:36.661
Oh, forget it. Forget it!

568
00:44:36.827 --> 00:44:39.956
It's gone. It's...

569
00:44:40.122 --> 00:44:42.966
Hmm. That's not bad.

570
00:44:46.295 --> 00:44:49.139
First, you take a chocolate bar.
Any bar'll do.


571
00:44:49.298 --> 00:44:50.845
- Oh.
- Do you mind if I, uh...


572
00:44:51.008 --> 00:44:52.510
No, knock yourself out, skipper.

573
00:44:53.302 --> 00:44:56.306
You crumble up the chocolate
into little pieces.


574
00:44:56.472 --> 00:44:59.851
Then you kind of stir it
into the ice cream. See?


575
00:45:00.017 --> 00:45:02.145
Yes, I see. What
do you call this again?

576
00:45:02.311 --> 00:45:04.905
Landslide. It's new. Very new.

577
00:45:05.064 --> 00:45:10.537
Mmm. Landslide. Topnotch. Mmm.

578
00:45:10.695 --> 00:45:15.371
You know, Hogarth, we live
in a strange and wondrous time.


579
00:45:15.533 --> 00:45:17.206
The Atomic Age.

580
00:45:17.368 --> 00:45:20.338
But there's a dark side
to progress, Hogarth.


581
00:45:20.496 --> 00:45:22.043
Ever hear of Sputnik?

582
00:45:22.206 --> 00:45:24.584
Yeah, it's the first satellite in space.

583
00:45:24.875 --> 00:45:28.550
Foreign satellite, Hogarth,
and all that that implies.


584
00:45:28.713 --> 00:45:31.387
Even now, it orbits overhead.

585
00:45:31.549 --> 00:45:33.176
Boop. Boop.

586
00:45:33.342 --> 00:45:35.219
Watching us.

587
00:45:35.386 --> 00:45:37.388
We can't see it, but it's there.

588
00:45:37.555 --> 00:45:40.058
Much like that giant thing in the woods.

589
00:45:40.391 --> 00:45:42.234
We don't know what it is
or what it can do.


590
00:45:42.393 --> 00:45:44.111
I don't feel safe, Hogarth.

591
00:45:44.270 --> 00:45:46.568
- Do you?
- What are you talking about?


592
00:45:46.731 --> 00:45:50.361
What am I talking about?
What am I talking about?


593
00:45:50.735 --> 00:45:53.238
I'm talking about
your goldarned security, Hogarth!


594
00:45:53.404 --> 00:45:55.247
While you're snoozing
in your little jammies,


595
00:45:55.406 --> 00:45:57.875
back in Washington,
we're wide-awake and worried. Why?


596
00:45:58.034 --> 00:46:00.913
Because everyone wants
what we have, Hogarth! Everyone!


597
00:46:01.078 --> 00:46:03.046
You think this metal man is fun.
But who built it?


598
00:46:03.205 --> 00:46:06.755
The Russians? The Chinese? Martians?
Canadians? I don't care!


599
00:46:06.917 --> 00:46:09.261
All I know is, we didn't build it,
and that's reason enough


600
00:46:09.420 --> 00:46:12.094
to assume the worst
and blow it to kingdom come!


601
00:46:12.256 --> 00:46:15.601
Now, you're going to tell me about
this thing. You're gonna lead me to it.


602
00:46:15.760 --> 00:46:18.229
And we are going to destroy it
before it destroys us!


603
00:46:20.890 --> 00:46:22.312
Just hold that thought
and stay right there.


604
00:46:22.475 --> 00:46:23.977
Oh-oh.

605
00:46:30.066 --> 00:46:31.818
Little lower. Little bit lower...

606
00:46:31.984 --> 00:46:34.612
Hey. I thought you were in trouble.

607
00:46:34.779 --> 00:46:36.156
That sucks. Let me just... Up a little.

608
00:46:36.322 --> 00:46:39.075
I had to ditch this weird guy
who's staying at our house.


609
00:46:39.241 --> 00:46:41.289
It took me hours to shake him!

610
00:46:41.452 --> 00:46:43.420
I kill myself to get out here!

611
00:46:43.579 --> 00:46:47.129
And you have him doing... 
Arts and crafts!

612
00:46:47.291 --> 00:46:50.090
You got a problem with
arts and crafts, little man?


613
00:46:50.252 --> 00:46:54.177
He's a giant robot, Dean.
It's a little undignified.


614
00:46:54.340 --> 00:46:57.810
Yeah? Well, smart guy,
what would you have him do?


615
00:47:01.680 --> 00:47:04.810
Main systems on. Main engines.

616
00:47:04.975 --> 00:47:06.648
One, two and three.

617
00:47:06.811 --> 00:47:12.489
All systems go.
Five, four, three two, one!


618
00:47:12.650 --> 00:47:13.947
Blast off!

619
00:47:24.995 --> 00:47:27.373
We're landing. 
We're landing!

620
00:47:27.540 --> 00:47:29.963
We're landing!

621
00:47:35.881 --> 00:47:38.350
Say, can you guys
cool yourselves a little?


622
00:47:38.509 --> 00:47:40.352
I feel like we're pressing our luck here.

623
00:47:40.511 --> 00:47:42.513
Hey, baby, we are cool!

624
00:47:42.680 --> 00:47:45.524
Welcome to downtown Coolsville.

625
00:47:45.683 --> 00:47:47.685
Population? Us.

626
00:47:47.852 --> 00:47:52.858
Well, can you move Coolsville
to someplace less conspicuous?


627
00:47:53.023 --> 00:47:55.993
- How about the lake?
- Okay.


628
00:47:56.152 --> 00:47:58.871
Aw, come with us. It'll be fun.

629
00:48:49.622 --> 00:48:53.593
This can't last forever, Hogarth.
We gotta tell somebody about him.


630
00:48:53.751 --> 00:48:55.594
Ah, you worry too much.

631
00:48:58.464 --> 00:49:01.434
Hey, Dean! Watch this!

632
00:49:01.592 --> 00:49:03.765
All right, we're watching. 
We're watching.

633
00:49:03.928 --> 00:49:07.102
This one's for professionals only!

634
00:49:08.933 --> 00:49:10.435
Banzai!

635
00:49:17.854 --> 00:49:22.075
Come on in! The water's great!

636
00:49:22.838 --> 00:49:24.115
No, thanks.

637
00:49:24.281 --> 00:49:26.283
You weenie!

638
00:49:27.952 --> 00:49:28.999
Come on in.

639
00:49:29.161 --> 00:49:32.256
It's really, really refreshing.

640
00:49:39.463 --> 00:49:42.012
What? You too?

641
00:49:42.174 --> 00:49:45.474
You big baby!

642
00:49:50.849 --> 00:49:52.817
Banzai!

643
00:50:24.883 --> 00:50:26.851
Whoo!

644
00:50:30.806 --> 00:50:32.353
- Hey.
- Yeah?


645
00:50:32.516 --> 00:50:35.395
- You're right in the middle of the road!
- Yeah?


646
00:50:35.561 --> 00:50:36.687
All right.

647
00:50:40.357 --> 00:50:44.032
I think that's enough fun for one day.

648
00:50:58.542 --> 00:51:00.544
Are you okay in there, Mr. Mansley?

649
00:51:00.711 --> 00:51:02.738
I'm back with the toilet paper you needed.

650
00:51:02.904 --> 00:51:06.225
Thanks! I think I'm feeling better now.

651
00:51:06.383 --> 00:51:09.011
Much. Much better.

652
00:51:17.019 --> 00:51:19.067
It's beautiful, huh?

653
00:51:19.229 --> 00:51:20.902
Hey, look!

654
00:51:22.566 --> 00:51:24.409
It's a deer.

655
00:51:24.568 --> 00:51:25.785
- Deer?
- Shh.


656
00:51:25.944 --> 00:51:27.571
Let's get closer.

657
00:52:00.646 --> 00:52:02.819
Hmm. Well, I guess he decided to...

658
00:52:11.782 --> 00:52:13.830
It's the monster!

659
00:52:16.912 --> 00:52:18.289
Oh, no.

660
00:52:25.963 --> 00:52:28.182
It's dead.

661
00:52:30.634 --> 00:52:31.806
Dead?

662
00:52:34.972 --> 00:52:36.440
Don't do that!

663
00:52:38.308 --> 00:52:39.480
Why?

664
00:52:39.643 --> 00:52:42.442
It's dead. Understand?

665
00:52:42.604 --> 00:52:45.983
They shot it with that gun.

666
00:52:55.033 --> 00:52:56.501
Hey, what's wrong?

667
00:52:58.495 --> 00:53:01.715
- Guns.
- Yes. Guns kill.


668
00:53:02.833 --> 00:53:05.507
Guns kill.

669
00:53:30.360 --> 00:53:34.831
I know you feel bad about the deer.
But it's not your fault.


670
00:53:34.990 --> 00:53:36.492
Things die.

671
00:53:36.658 --> 00:53:38.501
It's part of life.

672
00:53:38.660 --> 00:53:40.833
It's bad to kill.

673
00:53:40.996 --> 00:53:43.044
But it's not bad to die.

674
00:53:43.582 --> 00:53:45.755
You die?

675
00:53:45.918 --> 00:53:50.719
Well, yes, someday.

676
00:53:50.881 --> 00:53:53.179
I die?

677
00:53:53.342 --> 00:53:55.060
I don't know.

678
00:53:55.219 --> 00:53:59.690
You're made of metal
but you have feelings.


679
00:53:59.848 --> 00:54:01.896
And you think about things.

680
00:54:02.059 --> 00:54:05.108
And that means you have a soul.

681
00:54:05.270 --> 00:54:08.023
And souls don't die.

682
00:54:08.190 --> 00:54:10.067
Soul?

683
00:54:10.234 --> 00:54:14.239
Mom says it's something inside
of all good things,


684
00:54:14.404 --> 00:54:17.032
and that it goes on forever and ever.

685
00:54:31.755 --> 00:54:35.259
Souls don't die.

686
00:54:48.313 --> 00:54:50.281
You're very kind. 
Thank you so much.

687
00:54:52.150 --> 00:54:55.120
You ever seen a better picture than that?
Look at those details.


688
00:54:55.279 --> 00:54:58.954
This is the famous 60 second
Polaroid land camera.


689
00:54:59.324 --> 00:55:00.450
Seeing the results on the spot...

690
00:55:08.458 --> 00:55:09.675
In 60 seconds...

691
00:55:11.461 --> 00:55:13.936
You know, if you...

692
00:55:16.091 --> 00:55:17.638
Don't you remember anything?

693
00:55:25.684 --> 00:55:27.937
You saw me save you.

694
00:55:29.187 --> 00:55:31.906
You came from the sky, right?

695
00:55:35.986 --> 00:55:38.330
You don't even know where "he" came from.

696
00:55:38.488 --> 00:55:41.332
Or what the hell "he" is!

697
00:55:48.165 --> 00:55:50.167
Guess you're not gonna hurt me.

698
00:56:13.023 --> 00:56:15.250
You're late for dinner, Hogarth.

699
00:56:17.694 --> 00:56:19.992
Your mom's working late tonight, Hogarth.

700
00:56:20.322 --> 00:56:21.619
So it's just us guys.

701
00:56:21.782 --> 00:56:24.535
And we're gonna have a little chat.
Sit down!


702
00:56:26.036 --> 00:56:29.666
How's that? A little too bright? Good.

703
00:56:31.625 --> 00:56:35.004
Forgive me, Hogarth.
I wanted you to learn something.


704
00:56:35.170 --> 00:56:36.888
What can I learn from you?

705
00:56:37.047 --> 00:56:38.219
You can learn this, Hogarth.

706
00:56:38.382 --> 00:56:40.555
That I can do anything I want,
whenever I want,


707
00:56:40.717 --> 00:56:43.015
if I feel it's in
the people's best interest.


708
00:56:43.178 --> 00:56:45.306
The giant metal man, where is it?

709
00:56:45.472 --> 00:56:48.066
I don't know what you're talking about.

710
00:56:48.225 --> 00:56:50.068
You don't? Well.

711
00:56:51.728 --> 00:56:53.651
Does this ring a bell?

712
00:56:54.481 --> 00:56:55.698
No?

713
00:56:55.857 --> 00:56:57.234
How about this?

714
00:56:58.527 --> 00:57:00.404
You've been careless, Hogarth.

715
00:57:00.570 --> 00:57:01.913
It doesn't prove anything.

716
00:57:02.072 --> 00:57:04.666
It's enough to get the Army here
with one phone call.


717
00:57:04.825 --> 00:57:07.749
- Then what's stopping you?
- Where's the giant?


718
00:57:07.911 --> 00:57:10.209
You can't protect him, Hogarth,

719
00:57:10.372 --> 00:57:13.751
any more than you can protect your mother.

720
00:57:13.917 --> 00:57:15.089
My mom?

721
00:57:15.252 --> 00:57:17.721
Ah, it's difficult
to raise a boy all alone.


722
00:57:17.879 --> 00:57:19.256
We can make it more difficult.

723
00:57:19.423 --> 00:57:21.425
In fact, we can make it so difficult

724
00:57:21.591 --> 00:57:24.765
that it would be irresponsible
for us to leave you in her care


725
00:57:24.928 --> 00:57:26.896
and all that that implies.

726
00:57:27.055 --> 00:57:29.774
- You'll be taken away from her, Hogarth.
- You can't do that!


727
00:57:29.933 --> 00:57:32.561
Oh, we can. And we will.

728
00:57:36.606 --> 00:57:38.700
He's in the junkyard.

729
00:57:38.859 --> 00:57:41.112
McCoppin's Scrap, off Culver Road.

730
00:57:41.278 --> 00:57:45.784
The junkyard. Of course!
Food for the metal-eater.


731
00:57:46.116 --> 00:57:49.962
I wouldn't worry about this, Hogarth.
It isn't really happening.


732
00:57:50.120 --> 00:57:52.418
This is only a bad dream.

733
00:57:56.293 --> 00:57:59.797
Where's the giant?

734
00:57:59.963 --> 00:58:02.807
This is only a bad dream.

735
00:58:02.966 --> 00:58:04.309
Yes, sir.

736
00:58:04.468 --> 00:58:05.890
This thing is real, sir.

737
00:58:06.053 --> 00:58:08.932
I not only have incontrovertible
evidence, General,


738
00:58:09.097 --> 00:58:10.815
I know where it's hidden.

739
00:58:10.974 --> 00:58:12.317
I don't know who
built it, but it's here.

740
00:58:12.476 --> 00:58:15.070
It's massive
and we're running out of time.


741
00:58:15.228 --> 00:58:17.981
There's no doubt we should act.
The only question, sir, is...


742
00:58:18.148 --> 00:58:20.492
Can you afford not to?

743
00:58:20.650 --> 00:58:24.655
Excellent, sir. You won't regret it.
Thank you, sir.


744
00:58:35.332 --> 00:58:39.132
The Army arrives in the morning, Hogarth.
Don't get cute.


745
00:58:44.508 --> 00:58:46.010
I gotta warn Dean.

746
00:58:56.937 --> 00:58:59.360
I'll be watching you.

747
01:00:17.434 --> 01:00:18.686
Morning, Kent.

748
01:00:26.943 --> 01:00:31.449
For some reason, the Army
is in our front yard, Mr. Mansley.


749
01:00:31.615 --> 01:00:33.743
Please, call me Kent.

750
01:00:41.291 --> 01:00:43.589
Okay.

751
01:00:59.768 --> 01:01:01.987
- All right, where is it?
- What?


752
01:01:02.145 --> 01:01:04.113
You know darn well what. The monster.

753
01:01:04.272 --> 01:01:07.446
The giant thing. 
The metal man.

754
01:01:08.735 --> 01:01:13.616
Ah, the metal man. Jeez, you were
scaring me there for a second.


755
01:01:13.782 --> 01:01:16.831
I thought I was under attack or something.

756
01:01:16.993 --> 01:01:18.245
He's in the back.

757
01:01:18.411 --> 01:01:20.334
Come on. I'll show you.

758
01:01:25.835 --> 01:01:28.008
You guys got here just in time.

759
01:01:28.171 --> 01:01:30.970
This rich cat,
you know, some industrialist,


760
01:01:31.132 --> 01:01:33.430
wants him for the lobby of his company.

761
01:01:33.593 --> 01:01:35.516
He whipped out his checkbook on the spot.

762
01:01:35.679 --> 01:01:39.024
I said, "Hey, you got him
for the rest of your life.


763
01:01:39.182 --> 01:01:43.278
"But, what, I gotta let go the moment
I give birth? I mean, come on.


764
01:01:43.436 --> 01:01:45.689
"Give me some time
to cut the umbilical, man."


765
01:01:47.107 --> 01:01:48.609
Here he is.

766
01:01:54.948 --> 01:01:56.291
Anyway, I haven't sold him yet.

767
01:01:56.449 --> 01:02:00.875
So if you really want him and if,
you know, you throw in


768
01:02:01.037 --> 01:02:03.210
a competitive bid...

769
01:02:03.373 --> 01:02:05.125
Sir, I... Listen... 
Sir, listen...

770
01:02:05.292 --> 01:02:07.545
- Step outside, Mansley.
- Yes.


771
01:02:08.044 --> 01:02:10.888
You realize how much hardware
I brought out here?


772
01:02:11.047 --> 01:02:15.143
You just blew millions of Uncle Sam's
dollars out of your butt!


773
01:02:15.302 --> 01:02:18.055
I gotta admit, 
I'm relieved that

774
01:02:18.221 --> 01:02:20.565
this is what Hogarth was talking about.

775
01:02:20.724 --> 01:02:24.524
I mean, I was beginning to, um,
think it was real.


776
01:02:25.785 --> 01:02:27.906
I mean, don't get
me wrong, I like it.

777
01:02:28.064 --> 01:02:30.908
But, uh, do you need all this stuff
on the surface?


778
01:02:31.067 --> 01:02:34.571
Well, um, no, actually.

779
01:02:34.738 --> 01:02:37.742
It just sort of...
It seems kind of slapped on.


780
01:02:37.907 --> 01:02:40.205
You know, not as thought-out
as this other piece.


781
01:02:40.368 --> 01:02:43.087
- You like that one?
- Yeah.


782
01:02:44.706 --> 01:02:46.708
You'll be chief inspector
of subway toilets


783
01:02:46.875 --> 01:02:48.593
by the time I'm finished with you!

784
01:02:48.752 --> 01:02:53.098
Now, pack up. I'll expect you back
in Washington to clear out your office.


785
01:02:53.256 --> 01:02:54.553
Yes, sir.

786
01:02:57.260 --> 01:02:59.729
Hmm. I see why Hogarth sneaks out here.

787
01:02:59.888 --> 01:03:02.107
You mean, you know about that?

788
01:03:02.390 --> 01:03:04.233
Aw. Now I do.

789
01:03:18.406 --> 01:03:22.127
Bye, Kent, and all that that implies.

790
01:03:22.285 --> 01:03:23.878
Okay, you can move now.

791
01:03:25.455 --> 01:03:26.798
Nice job!

792
01:03:32.128 --> 01:03:33.801
Thruster to base.

793
01:03:33.963 --> 01:03:35.636
I'm goin' in.

794
01:03:35.799 --> 01:03:38.803
Only one creature could create
so much destruction.


795
01:03:38.968 --> 01:03:40.766
The hideous, people-eating,

796
01:03:40.929 --> 01:03:44.274
killing machine, Atomo!

797
01:03:45.767 --> 01:03:47.644
Atomo?

798
01:03:47.811 --> 01:03:49.813
No Atomo.

799
01:03:58.238 --> 01:04:00.161
I Superman.

800
01:04:00.323 --> 01:04:02.417
Okay, Superman.

801
01:04:02.575 --> 01:04:03.827
Take this!

802
01:04:07.831 --> 01:04:09.174
Stupid gun.

803
01:04:22.137 --> 01:04:23.810
Hey. What's wrong?

804
01:04:26.474 --> 01:04:28.977
As I was saying, take this!

805
01:04:32.647 --> 01:04:34.024
Oh!

806
01:04:35.191 --> 01:04:36.363
What happened? 
What was that...

807
01:04:36.526 --> 01:04:38.949
Shh. Stay down and follow me.

808
01:04:43.158 --> 01:04:44.535
Shh.

809
01:04:45.535 --> 01:04:46.878
Get back!

810
01:04:49.706 --> 01:04:52.050
I said, get back! I mean it!

811
01:04:52.876 --> 01:04:54.878
No, stop. Why?

812
01:04:55.044 --> 01:04:57.217
It was an accident. 
He's our friend.

813
01:04:57.380 --> 01:05:01.180
He's a piece of hardware, Hogarth.
Why do you think the Army was here?


814
01:05:01.342 --> 01:05:04.812
He's a weapon! 
A big gun that walks!

815
01:05:06.890 --> 01:05:08.392
I, I...

816
01:05:08.558 --> 01:05:10.060
I not gun.

817
01:05:10.226 --> 01:05:12.069
Yeah, what's that, huh?

818
01:05:12.562 --> 01:05:15.236
You almost did that to Hogarth!

819
01:05:16.399 --> 01:05:17.742
No.

820
01:05:21.321 --> 01:05:22.743
- Come back!
- Hogarth.


821
01:05:22.906 --> 01:05:24.533
- Hey, stop!
- Giant!


822
01:05:24.699 --> 01:05:26.201
Come back!

823
01:05:30.497 --> 01:05:32.090
It was defensive.

824
01:05:32.248 --> 01:05:34.501
He reacted to the gun.

825
01:05:37.712 --> 01:05:39.931
You're not gonna
get there fast enough on foot.


826
01:05:59.776 --> 01:06:02.279
See, I told you
it was a big hoax.

827
01:06:02.445 --> 01:06:04.072
- Dad said...
- Give me the binoculars.


828
01:06:04.239 --> 01:06:06.708
- What? What?
- Hey, there it is. I see it!


829
01:06:07.784 --> 01:06:09.707
It's big. It's walking away.

830
01:06:09.869 --> 01:06:12.042
- Hey. Gimme those.
- Over there. See it?


831
01:06:12.205 --> 01:06:13.627
The monster! Holy cow!

832
01:06:15.291 --> 01:06:16.463
Watch it!

833
01:06:16.626 --> 01:06:17.969
Help!

834
01:06:18.127 --> 01:06:19.970
Somebody help me!

835
01:06:20.630 --> 01:06:22.132
- I don't wanna fall!
- Help!


836
01:06:24.425 --> 01:06:25.551
I'm slipping!

837
01:06:25.718 --> 01:06:27.971
I can't hold on much longer!

838
01:06:36.980 --> 01:06:38.482
- Dad!
- Daddy!


839
01:06:40.984 --> 01:06:43.612
- He saved those boys!
- It's friendly!


840
01:06:59.126 --> 01:07:00.254
What...

841
01:07:03.006 --> 01:07:04.303
Oh!

842
01:07:06.009 --> 01:07:07.181
Stop! Look!

843
01:07:07.343 --> 01:07:09.846
Look behind you!
The giant, it's attacking!


844
01:07:10.013 --> 01:07:11.811
It's stomping the town! I was right!

845
01:07:11.973 --> 01:07:14.977
- Sweet mother of God.
- Look, damn you!


846
01:07:22.692 --> 01:07:25.866
I am not a gun.

847
01:07:33.953 --> 01:07:35.830
Hey, Mom.

848
01:07:49.385 --> 01:07:50.637
Let's get out of here!

849
01:07:50.803 --> 01:07:51.975
Run!

850
01:08:03.316 --> 01:08:05.865
Hey. Stop! There's a kid in his hands!

851
01:08:06.027 --> 01:08:07.404
Stop shooting!

852
01:08:08.404 --> 01:08:10.702
Kent! He only reacts defensively.

853
01:08:10.865 --> 01:08:14.085
If you don't shoot, he's harmless.
You gotta tell the General!


854
01:08:14.243 --> 01:08:16.371
This is all your fault, beatnik.
If you hadn't...


855
01:08:16.537 --> 01:08:17.709
Would you shut up and listen?

856
01:08:17.872 --> 01:08:21.217
You've gotta make them stop.
The giant's got the kid with him.


857
01:08:22.251 --> 01:08:23.423
I'll take care of it.

858
01:08:28.883 --> 01:08:33.354
He says the monster's killed a kid.
Sir, we must stop it at all costs.


859
01:08:33.513 --> 01:08:35.936
Go to code red. 
Repeat, code red!

860
01:08:37.392 --> 01:08:40.066
Mr. President, we have a situation, sir.

861
01:08:46.401 --> 01:08:48.699
Watch it, lady!

862
01:09:01.082 --> 01:09:03.210
Look out for the bus!

863
01:09:17.473 --> 01:09:18.975
You can fly?

864
01:09:20.935 --> 01:09:22.733
You can fly!

865
01:09:28.651 --> 01:09:29.994
Hogarth!

866
01:09:31.446 --> 01:09:34.620
Try pointing your arms straight ahead,
like Superman!


867
01:09:52.967 --> 01:09:54.594
No, no!

868
01:10:01.267 --> 01:10:03.611
I've lost visual. 
Repeat, lost visual!

869
01:10:08.524 --> 01:10:10.697
Man, that was close!

870
01:10:13.946 --> 01:10:15.198
No!

871
01:10:17.283 --> 01:10:19.331
Ha. Gotcha!

872
01:10:36.969 --> 01:10:38.892
Good call, Mansley.

873
01:10:39.055 --> 01:10:43.731
Secure the area. Let's find out
what this thing is and who sent it.


874
01:10:50.525 --> 01:10:51.651
Huh?

875
01:11:06.707 --> 01:11:08.550
Halt! Set your perimeter!

876
01:11:09.836 --> 01:11:12.259
- It's still alive!
- Shoot at it!


877
01:11:35.570 --> 01:11:36.947
Retreat! Retreat!

878
01:11:38.865 --> 01:11:40.583
Let's get out of here!

879
01:11:50.418 --> 01:11:52.045
Hogarth!

880
01:11:53.462 --> 01:11:56.432
He's unconscious, but he's okay.
Let's get him in the car.


881
01:11:56.799 --> 01:11:59.598
Drive, baby, drive! Step on it! Floor it!

882
01:11:59.760 --> 01:12:03.310
It's gaining on us. Faster! Faster! Hurry!

883
01:12:13.274 --> 01:12:15.117
All battleships fire at the robot!

884
01:12:15.276 --> 01:12:16.448
Now!

885
01:12:16.611 --> 01:12:18.238
Now, damn it, now!

886
01:12:26.495 --> 01:12:29.465
Nothing can stop this thing!
We've hit it with everything we've got!


887
01:12:29.624 --> 01:12:31.592
Not everything, General. The bomb.

888
01:12:33.294 --> 01:12:35.968
The Nautilus has first strike capability
and is not far offshore.


889
01:12:36.964 --> 01:12:38.261
You scare me, Mansley.

890
01:12:38.424 --> 01:12:41.177
You want us to bomb ourselves
in order to kill it?


891
01:12:41.344 --> 01:12:43.688
General, the giant seems to follow
whatever attacks it.


892
01:12:43.846 --> 01:12:46.599
We can lure it away from the town,
then destroy it.


893
01:12:48.351 --> 01:12:51.981
Radio the Nautilus. Tell them to target
the robot and await my command.


894
01:12:53.773 --> 01:12:56.196
This is Nautilus.
What is the giant's current position?


895
01:12:56.359 --> 01:12:59.033
67. 71972 degrees west,

896
01:12:59.195 --> 01:13:02.199
by 44.50177 degrees north.

897
01:13:02.365 --> 01:13:03.491
Locked and loaded.

898
01:13:03.699 --> 01:13:05.372
Oh, my baby, I'm so sorry.

899
01:13:05.534 --> 01:13:07.832
- Stop the car.
- Hogarth! My God, honey, you're all right.


900
01:13:07.995 --> 01:13:09.542
Go back! We've gotta help him!

901
01:13:09.705 --> 01:13:12.003
Are you crazy, kid?
You're lucky to be alive!


902
01:13:12.166 --> 01:13:13.713
We're taking you to a hospital.

903
01:13:19.715 --> 01:13:21.717
Everyone! Out of the car!
We're evacuating the area.


904
01:13:21.884 --> 01:13:23.978
What are you talking about?
We gotta get this boy to a hospital.


905
01:13:24.136 --> 01:13:25.308
What boy?

906
01:13:25.972 --> 01:13:27.189
Hogarth!

907
01:13:31.018 --> 01:13:32.361
Hogarth, no!

908
01:13:42.571 --> 01:13:45.074
Hey! No! Stop!

909
01:13:56.377 --> 01:13:57.674
This is General Rogard.

910
01:13:57.837 --> 01:14:00.431
Ready the attack and prepare
to retreat to the fallback position.


911
01:14:00.589 --> 01:14:04.093
No! No! Stop! My son is out there!

912
01:14:06.679 --> 01:14:10.104
No, wait. It's me, Hogarth. Remember?

913
01:14:10.766 --> 01:14:14.737
It's bad to kill. Guns kill.

914
01:14:14.895 --> 01:14:17.239
And you don't have to be a gun.

915
01:14:17.690 --> 01:14:20.239
You are what you choose to be.

916
01:14:20.860 --> 01:14:22.828
You choose.

917
01:14:23.738 --> 01:14:25.081
Choose.

918
01:14:26.323 --> 01:14:28.496
Hogarth.

919
01:14:36.292 --> 01:14:37.794
It's okay. It's okay.

920
01:14:38.169 --> 01:14:40.263
We gotta show them you're good.

921
01:14:44.258 --> 01:14:46.260
Nautilus to Rogard,
missile armed and ready.


922
01:14:46.427 --> 01:14:48.054
What are you saying, he's friendly?

923
01:14:48.220 --> 01:14:50.769
Yes. Attacking him is triggering
a defense mechanism.


924
01:14:50.931 --> 01:14:53.684
Don't listen, General! Destroy the monster
while we still have the chance!


925
01:14:56.145 --> 01:14:58.443
General, you shoot and the whole thing
starts all over again.


926
01:14:58.606 --> 01:15:01.200
- Stop it now! Our future's at stake!
- Orders, sir?


927
01:15:01.358 --> 01:15:03.452
Which is why you have
got to stop, General!


928
01:15:03.611 --> 01:15:06.865
- It's getting closer! Orders, sir?
- Don't shoot! Don't shoot!


929
01:15:07.031 --> 01:15:09.625
- Hogarth!
- Hold your fire! The boy's alive?


930
01:15:09.784 --> 01:15:11.036
It's a trick! Launch the missile.

931
01:15:11.202 --> 01:15:13.079
Are you mad, Mansley?

932
01:15:13.245 --> 01:15:14.872
All units, stand down!

933
01:15:15.039 --> 01:15:17.087
Rogard to Nautilus. Come in, Nautilus.

934
01:15:17.249 --> 01:15:19.047
This is Nautilus standing by.

935
01:15:19.210 --> 01:15:20.462
Launch the missile now!

936
01:15:28.302 --> 01:15:31.181
That missile is targeted
to the giant's current position!


937
01:15:31.639 --> 01:15:33.391
Where's the giant, Mansley?

938
01:15:33.974 --> 01:15:37.569
What... Oh...

939
01:15:37.728 --> 01:15:40.151
We can duck and cover.
There's a fallout shelter right there.


940
01:15:40.314 --> 01:15:42.988
There's no way to survive this, you idiot!

941
01:15:43.150 --> 01:15:45.027
You mean, we're all going to...

942
01:15:45.194 --> 01:15:48.573
To die, Mansley, for our country.

943
01:15:49.657 --> 01:15:52.752
Screw our country! 
I want to live!

944
01:15:58.207 --> 01:15:59.333
Hold him, men.

945
01:15:59.500 --> 01:16:02.720
Make sure he stays here,
like a good soldier.


946
01:16:06.674 --> 01:16:07.846
Oh!

947
01:16:12.003 --> 01:16:13.752
Oh, no.

948
01:16:16.225 --> 01:16:18.569
- Hmm?
- It's a missile.


949
01:16:18.727 --> 01:16:23.107
When it comes down everyone will die.

950
01:16:23.274 --> 01:16:24.651
There it is!

951
01:16:40.833 --> 01:16:43.757
- Shouldn't we get to a shelter?
- It wouldn't matter.


952
01:16:44.378 --> 01:16:46.551
I fix.

953
01:16:53.220 --> 01:16:54.517
Giant?

954
01:16:58.684 --> 01:17:00.231
Hogarth.

955
01:17:01.353 --> 01:17:03.981
You stay.

956
01:17:04.899 --> 01:17:07.618
I go.

957
01:17:12.573 --> 01:17:16.123
No following.

958
01:17:25.669 --> 01:17:27.012
I love you.

959
01:17:55.491 --> 01:17:57.368
You are who you choose to be.

960
01:18:00.329 --> 01:18:02.707
Superman.

961
01:18:34.655 --> 01:18:36.123
Let's go home.

962
01:19:23.037 --> 01:19:26.166
Your best work yet, honey.
No doubt about it.


963
01:19:26.332 --> 01:19:28.710
You think this is my best? Really?

964
01:19:28.876 --> 01:19:32.676
Well, you know,
next to that bug, uh, thing.


965
01:19:32.838 --> 01:19:36.383
You know, the one with the, uh, shovels...

966
01:19:36.742 --> 01:19:40.313
Um, Hogarth? Come on, honey. Time to go.

967
01:19:40.471 --> 01:19:43.224
- See you later, guys.
- See you later, Hogarth.


968
01:19:43.390 --> 01:19:45.813
Oh, hey, Hogarth, um,
the General sent this to you.


969
01:19:45.976 --> 01:19:47.193
What is it?

970
01:19:47.353 --> 01:19:49.731
He said it was the only part recovered.

971
01:19:50.147 --> 01:19:52.195
He thought you should have it.

972
01:19:54.151 --> 01:19:55.744
I miss him.

973
01:20:44.952 --> 01:20:46.420
See you later!